Pickle%20is%20honestly%20the%20ultimate%20girl%20math%2C%26quot%3B%20Creatore%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20thinking%20in%20terms%20of%20wears%2C%20I%20think%2C%20'I'm%20going%20to%20make%20this%20investment%20in%20terms%20of%20rentals.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPickle%20was%20founded%20by%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffavorite-financial-firms-survey-across-investment-banking-pe-hedge-funds-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlackstone%3C%2Fa%3E%20employees%20Brian%20McMahon%20and%20Julia%20O'Mara.%20After%20launching%20its%20app%20in%202022%2C%20Pickle%20tapped%20New%20York%20City%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-ways-to-make-money-as-content-creator%3Fr%3Dhow-to-become-an-influencer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einfluencers%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20growth.%20In%202023%2C%20it%20opened%20its%20first%20brick-and-mortar%20store%20in%20New%20York%20and%20has%20since%20expanded%20to%20markets%20like%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20Miami.%20The%20startup%20has%20also%20raised%20%2420%20million%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPickle's%20top%2010%20%26quot%3Blenders%26quot%3B%20earned%20an%20average%20of%20%243%2C200%20a%20month%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company%2C%20which%20takes%20a%2020%25%20cut%20of%20transactions%20in%20the%20app%20(and%2035%25%20of%20transactions%20from%20their%20in-person%20shop).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kana%20Kozlowski%20next%20to%20a%20rack%20of%20clothing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f73bfc6ad288d1481b102%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKana%20Kozlowski%20has%20featured%20some%20clothing%20at%20a%20Pickle%20pop-up%20event%20in%20LA.%3Cp%3EKana%20Kozlowski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20spoke%20with%20five%20women%20about%20how%20much%20money%20they've%20made%20renting%20out%20their%20clothes%20on%20Pickle%2C%20how%20they've%20built%20bustling%20side-hustles%2C%20and%20their%20strategies%20for%20getting%20the%20most%20out%20of%20their%20unworn%20clothes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b425933-6885-4757-9a05-ceb952242c7a%5C%22%3ESome%20are%20earning%20thousands%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreatore%20started%20renting%20on%20Pickle%20in%20July%20and%20listed%20only%20a%20few%20items.%20Less%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20she%20made%20%2412%2C797%20in%20April%20alone.%20She%20now%20typically%20earns%20between%20%247%2C000%20and%20%2412%2C000%20each%20busy%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20verified%20Creatore's%20and%20the%20four%20other%20Pickle%20lenders'%20earnings%20with%20documentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsabella%20De%20Murguia%2C%2026%20and%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20works%20in%20consulting%20and%20devotes%20around%20four%20hours%20a%20week%20to%20her%20Pickle%20side-hustle%2C%20not%20including%20laundry.%20She%20opened%20her%20closet%20in%202023%20after%20seeing%20ads%20for%20the%20app%20on%20TikTok%2C%20and%20now%20makes%20between%20%243%2C000%20and%20%244%2C000%20a%20month%20during%20peak%20rental%20seasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJess%20Work%2C%2026%2C%20works%20full-time%20in%20fashion%20while%20balancing%20a%20part-time%20job%20as%20a%20content%20creator.%20On%20average%2C%20she%20earns%20between%20%243%2C000%20and%20%244%2C000%20from%20her%20rentals.%20Some%20months%2C%20like%20around%20the%20holidays%2C%20she%20can%20make%20about%20%246%2C000%20from%20the%20app%2C%20Work%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20has%20a%20total%20of%20229%20listings%20on%20Pickle%2C%20which%20range%20from%20%2415%20to%20%24215%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20expensive%20item%20being%20a%20limited%20edition%20silver%20dress%20from%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcos-popular-menswear-fragrance-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EH%26amp%3BM%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecollaboration.%20Work%20said%20the%20dress%20has%20been%20rented%20a%20handful%20of%20times%20since%20she%20listed%20it%20six%20months%20ago%2C%20dubbing%20it%20the%20%26quot%3Bsisterhood%20of%20the%20sparkly%20dress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jess%20Work's%20most%20expensive%20listing%20on%20Pickle%20is%20a%20sparkly%2C%20silver%20dress.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6830be9a6ffb6822ec61634c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJess%20Work's%20most%20expensive%20listing%20on%20Pickle%20is%20a%20sparkly%2C%20silver%20dress.%3Cp%3EJess%20Work%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20those%20who%20aren't%20hitting%20four%20and%20five%20figures%20can%20earn%20a%20sizable%20chunk%20of%20change.%20Andrea%20Duffield%2C%20a%2031-year-old%20entrepreneur%20in%20Miami%2C%20makes%20between%20%24600%20and%20%24800%20each%20month%2C%20which%20is%20helpful%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20in%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-secondhand-clothing-industry-thrift-charity-stores-goodwill-thredup-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomy%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20photographer%20and%20bartender%20Kana%20Kozlowski%2C%2026%2C%20has%20been%20renting%20for%20around%20a%20year.%20She%20earns%20between%20%24200%20and%20%24500%20most%20months%2C%20but%20saw%20a%20bump%20during%20Coachella.%20Across%20the%20platform%2C%20Pickle%20has%20had%20spikes%20in%20rentals%20around%20holidays%20like%20Halloween%2C%20or%20seasonal%20categories%20like%20skiing%20gear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPickle%20also%20helps%20its%20lenders%20price%20their%20rentals%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20listed%20at%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20the%20original%20retail%20price%2C%20McMahon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287b5d897-19cb-4bbd-960f-a1d796c123d5%5C%22%3ERentals%20are%20paying%20the%20bills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20Pickle%20earnings%20go%20toward%20everyday%20expenses%20and%20bills.%20De%20Murguia%20said%20the%20app%20helps%20her%20hit%20savings%20goals%20and%20afford%20social%20outings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20tough%20to%20get%20joy%20from%20being%20a%20full-time%20creative%20when%20you're%20worried%20about%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Creatore%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20really%20given%20me%20that%20peace%20of%20mind%20again%20to%20fall%20back%20in%20love%20with%20blogging%20and%20photography.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuffield%20recently%20founded%20her%20own%20company%20and%20said%20everything%20she%20makes%20from%20Pickle%20goes%20back%20into%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22112092fa-00ad-44a7-9f48-a25de204fc56%5C%22%3EKeeping%20up%20a%20Pickle%20closet%20takes%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20New%20Yorkers%2C%20De%20Murguia%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20storage%20space%20%E2%80%94%20four%20closets%20go%20to%20herself%20and%20her%20Pickle%20inventory%2C%20and%20one%20goes%20to%20her%20boyfriend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Closet%20full%20of%20clothes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f7534ca50259add4cd2c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDe%20Murguia%20has%20four%20closets%20devoted%20to%20herself%20and%20her%20Pickle.%3Cp%3EIsabella%20De%20Murguia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPickle%20has%20changed%20the%20way%20lenders%20shop.%20Four%20of%20the%20women%20BI%20spoke%20said%20they%20now%20buy%20items%20with%20the%20intent%20of%20renting%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20buy%20something%20maybe%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20bought%20previously%2C%26quot%3B%20Work%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20I'll%20be%20able%20to%20hopefully%20make%20more%20or%20at%20least%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20item.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreatore%20said%20she%20has%20a%20spreadsheet%20to%20map%20out%20purchase%2C%20rental%2C%20and%20maintenance%20costs%2C%20and%20De%20Murguia%20returns%20anything%20that%20doesn't%20rent%20within%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20inventory%20flowing%20also%20comes%20at%20a%20cost.%20Work%20estimated%20that%20she%20spends%20between%20%241%2C000%20and%20%242%2C000%20each%20month%20on%20new%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertain%20items%20are%20pretty%20much%20guaranteed%20to%20do%20well%2C%20the%20lenders%20told%20BI%3A%20pieces%20that%20are%20sold%20out%2C%20were%20seen%20on%20a%20celebrity%2C%20or%20come%20from%20certain%20brands%2C%20like%20Rat%20%26amp%3B%20Boa%20and%20Frankies%20Bikinis.%20Part%20of%20being%20successful%20is%20about%20knowing%20what's%20likely%20to%20go%20viral%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20something%20starts%20to%20get%20really%20popular%20in%20a%20particular%20market%20or%20on%20social%20media%2C%20it's%20typically%20on%20Pickle%20right%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20McMahon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20De%20Murguia%20put%20it%2C%20the%20potential%20success%20for%20those%20with%20closet%20savvy%20is%20huge%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20probably%20call%20it%20an%20enterprise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpickle-clothing-rental-side-hustle-influencer-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748081941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f7fd86ffb6822ec614706%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpickle-clothing-rental-side-hustle-influencer-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BI%20spoke%20with%20five%20women%20who%20rent%20clothing%20on%20the%20app%20Pickle%20about%20their%20earnings%2C%20strategies%2C%20and%20putting%20their%20clothes%20to%20the%20most%20profitable%20use.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22atecotzky%40businessinsider.com%20(Alice%20Tecotzky%2CSydney%20Bradley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A96%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.c